WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.820
Oops, here we go. Okay. All right. These are my conflicts. So today I'm going to be talking

00:00:07.820 --> 00:00:13.480
mostly about CD19 CAR-T in the setting of autoimmune disorders. We'll try to cover a few

00:00:13.480 --> 00:00:18.960
things, mechanisms, why that works, go over some clinical data, and where the field is moving

00:00:18.960 --> 00:00:26.540
forward. So as we all know, autoimmune conditions, many of them, the auto-regulation, auto-reactive

00:00:26.540 --> 00:00:34.300
B-cells play a central role in those conditions. Because of that, CD19 as a target will be

00:00:34.300 --> 00:00:42.000
attractive. B-cells lineage express widely C19. So knocking down the C19 B-cells, allowing for

00:00:42.000 --> 00:00:47.820
naive B-cell reconstitutions, can basically eliminate the need of lifelong immune suppression

00:00:47.820 --> 00:00:54.240
for those patients and reset their immune system. We used to do auto-transplant and we still do

00:00:54.240 --> 00:00:56.520
sometimes auto-transplant for some auto-regulation.

00:00:56.540 --> 00:01:00.860
In the case of autoimmune conditions, like scleroderma, on study we went for multiple

00:01:00.860 --> 00:01:07.620
sclerosis, compared to auto-transplant, where we do basically wide ablation of the immune

00:01:07.620 --> 00:01:11.980
system, here we try to be more targeted to the B-cell. The difference between CAR-T and

00:01:11.980 --> 00:01:17.980
auto-transplant, as we all know, is less chemotherapy upfront, possibly outpatients. So far, no

00:01:17.980 --> 00:01:23.080
treatment-related mortality being reported. And again, more focus on the B-cell lineage

00:01:23.080 --> 00:01:24.440
and less cytopenia.

00:01:25.120 --> 00:01:26.520
And we'll see if it's going to translate into auto-regulation.

00:01:26.540 --> 00:01:29.200
We will see if it's going to translate into less relapse with CAR-T.

00:01:29.200 --> 00:01:37.060
To kind of set standards, in Germany, there was a university, it's Langen, where it started

00:01:37.060 --> 00:01:43.120
initially with first reports, where they reported their own CAR-T experience with five patients

00:01:43.120 --> 00:01:48.640
received with SLE, and showed 100% response in those patients. From that, there was a

00:01:48.640 --> 00:01:53.860
big paper in Nature. A year later, in New England Drug Medicine, they have expansion

00:01:53.860 --> 00:01:55.120
for their own experience with SLE, myositis, and Zinc.

00:01:55.120 --> 00:01:55.620
Thank you.

00:01:56.540 --> 00:02:01.620
scleroderma, with again showing that all patients end up discontinuing immune suppressions after

00:02:01.620 --> 00:02:06.220
they received CA-19 CAR. From there, they took it further when they have the first prospective

00:02:06.220 --> 00:02:11.600
trials, where they showed 24 patients across different conditions, SLE, scleroderma, and

00:02:11.600 --> 00:02:19.660
myositis, achieved 92% achieved disease-specific remissions, and patients remained steroid-free

00:02:19.660 --> 00:02:27.160
at six months. So, from that, CASTEL study was kind of set standards to move forward

00:02:27.160 --> 00:02:34.780
with different companies that have interest in that field. Not only in rheumatology, but

00:02:34.780 --> 00:02:40.820
also in neurology, there is experience with myasthenia gravis and with multiple sclerosis.

00:02:40.820 --> 00:02:46.040
There was a very nice paper that came up in Nature, where we used a study called the SCARTED

00:02:46.040 --> 00:02:49.640
study, where we used a very novel CAR-BCM, which was a very novel study, and we used

00:02:49.640 --> 00:02:55.660
B-CMA-driven CAR-C, compared that to placebo, and was a randomized trial, where they showed

00:02:55.660 --> 00:03:02.020
that improvement of the symptoms in that very tough disease to treat, with no chemotherapy

00:03:02.020 --> 00:03:06.760
outpatient administrations and no CRS or ICANN. And now that study is moving toward the phase

00:03:06.760 --> 00:03:13.160
two, phase three trials, OROT, called OROT trials, were looking at the same conditions

00:03:13.160 --> 00:03:19.620
with the B-CMA-CAR-C. Most of the sclerosis, less experience with that. We're still doing transplants

00:03:19.620 --> 00:03:24.680
on clinical trials. We have BMT CTN trial, where we enroll patients with the standard

00:03:24.680 --> 00:03:30.200
of care. Earlier experience with the multiple sclerosis, or the transplant, showed to be

00:03:30.200 --> 00:03:35.100
superior to standard of care at that time, when they're randomized in a prior clinical

00:03:35.100 --> 00:03:42.640
trial called MIST trial. In multiple sclerosis, uniquely, T-cells had

00:03:42.640 --> 00:03:48.140
an important role, so knocking down the B-cells, not really, but potentially, will eliminate

00:03:48.140 --> 00:03:49.480
the problems.

00:03:49.480 --> 00:03:54.720
This was presented in tandem. We participated in the trial called BREAK-FREE trial, where

00:03:54.720 --> 00:04:01.980
basically, it's a lysosol-derived CAR called now ZOLA cell, where CD19 CAR, 4-1-B-B trials

00:04:01.980 --> 00:04:07.000
have two trials. One of them's for rheumatoid arthritis, and the other one's for rheumatoid

00:04:07.000 --> 00:04:12.100
conditions, other one for neurological condition, BREAK-FREE-1, BREAK-FREE-2. Data from the

00:04:12.100 --> 00:04:18.500
phase one trials of those two trials was presented at a tandem, where a combined of 83 patients,

00:04:18.500 --> 00:04:19.340
with different symptoms.

